subparagraph.content:
a College Council which shall be the executive body of the College administering
          the property and managing the general affairs of the College subject to the directions of
          the Board of Governors;

paragraph.content:
no act or resolution of any College body shall be invalid by reason only of any
        vacancy in, or any want of qualifications by or validity in the election or appointment of
        any member of such body;

subparagraph.content:
the College bodies specified in paragraph (a) may establish such committees as they
          see
          fit;

save for termination at the end of a period of probation the appointment of a
          teacher may be terminated by the College Council for good cause only, and in every case
          the College Council shall consider the recommendations of the Academic Board;

teachers in receipt of full time salaries from the College shall not engage in
          outside practice for reward without the consent of the College Council and subject to such
          conditions as it may impose;
